                              APPENDIX C

       EXAMPLE PROGRAM TO OBTAIN THE CONSTANTS OF AN EPHEMERIS



The program JPLCONST (both the Fortran source and the executable image
are in JPLDIR) demonstrates the use of the XCONST subroutine.  Once
compiled, and linked with JPLDIR:JPL/L, it can be run as follows:

     1.  $ ASSIGN/USER JPLDIR:DE200.DAT FOR012

     2.  $ RUN JPLDIR:JPLCONST

JPLCONST uses the XCONST subroutine to list all the constants of the
ephemeris on Fortran unit 12.  See also the Fortran source of the
PLEPH subroutine, which shows how the data output by XCONST can be
searched for named constants.

The Fortran source of JPLCONST follows.
























                                - 14 -
EXAMPLE PROGRAM TO OBTAIN THE CONSTANTS OF AN EPHEMERIS       Page C-2


      PROGRAM JPLCONST

*+
*
*  - - - - - - - - -
*   J P L C O N S T
*  - - - - - - - - -
*
*  Example program using the JPL routine XCONST.
*
*  I/O unit 12 is used to read the disc form of the ephemeris
*  file, output by the JPLREAD66 or JPLSHORT programs.
*
*
*  P.T.Wallace   Starlink   December 1985
*
*+

      IMPLICIT NONE

*  Array for 6-character names (with 2 trailing spaces)
      INTEGER NAM(2,300)
*  Arrays for data values
      DOUBLE PRECISION VAL(300)
      DOUBLE PRECISION SS(6)
*  Number of data values and counter
      INTEGER N

      INTEGER I,J



*  Pick up the information
      CALL XCONST(NAM,VAL,SS,N)

*  Report (note 'Hollerith' technique for NAM array)
      DO I=1,N
         WRITE (*,'(1X,I3,4X,A4,A2,4X,D20.14)')
     :                         I,(NAM(J,I),J=1,2),VAL(I)
      END DO
      DO I=1,6
         PRINT *,SS(I)
      END DO

      END








